                      LAB EXERCISES
EX.NO:04
            TABLE TAGS AND INTERNAL STYLE SHEETS
AIM:
  To develop a web page using CSS to create a timetable for the class using different border style.
PROCEDURE:
1.	Start the notepad and write HTML document with <html> tag.
2.	Create a head section using <head> tag and set a title using the <title> tag.
3.	Start the body section using <body> tag.
4.	Use the <style> tag to write internal CSS.
5.  Style the table with different border styles (solid, dashed, dotted, double).
6.  Add border width, color, padding, and text alignment in CSS.
7.  Insert a heading like <h1> or <h2> in the body.
8.  Create a <table> with rows and columns for the timetable.
9.  Fill in days and time slots; use colspan or rowspan for breaks or lab hours.
10. Save the file with a .html extension and open it in a browser to view the timetable.
PROGRAM:  
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html lang="en">
  <head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Class Timetable</title>
  <style>
  body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
  margin: 20px;
  }
  table {
  width: 80%;
  margin: 0 auto;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  background-color: #fff;
  border: 2px solid #004080;
  }
  th, td {
  padding: 10px;
  text-align: center;
  border: 1.5px solid #004080;
  }
  th {
  background-color: #004080;
  color: white;
  }
  tr:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  }
  </style>
  </head>
  <body>
  <h2>Second Computer Timetable</h2>
  <table>
  <tr>
  <th>Time</th>
  <th>Monday</th>
  <th>Tuesday</th>
  <th>Wednesday</th>
  <th>Thursday</th>
  <th>Friday</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>I Hour</td>
  <td>RDBMS</td>
  <td>BDLD</td>
  <td>ITE</td>
  <td>WEB</td>
  <td>OS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>II Hour</td>
  <td>CP</td>
  <td>GAM</td>
  <td>RDBMS</td>
  <td>BDLD</td>
  <td>ITE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>III Hour</td>
  <td>WEB</td>
  <td>OS</td>
  <td>CP</td>
  <td>GAM</td>
  <td>RDBMS</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>IV Hour</td>
  <td>BDLD</td>
  <td>ITE</td>
  <td>WEB</td>
  <td>OS</td>
  <td>CP</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>V Hour</td>
  <td>GAM</td>
  <td>RDBMS</td>
  <td>BDLD</td>
  <td>ITE</td>
  <td>WEB</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>VI Hour</td>
  <td>OS</td>
  <td>CP</td>
  <td>OS</td>
  <td>RDBMS</td>
  <td>BDLD</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
  <td>VII Hour</td>
  <td>ITE</td>
  <td>WEB</td>
  <td>OS</td>
  <td>CP</td>
  <td>GAM</td>
  </tr>
  </table>
  </body>
  </html>
RESULT:
     Thus the above HTML Code is executed and the output is obtained.
